taxon.wikipedia_summary: The willet (Tringa semipalmata), formerly in the monotypic genus Catoptrophorus as Catoptrophorus semipalmatus, is a large shorebird in the Scolopacidae family. It is a relatively large and robust sandpiper, and is the largest of the species called "shanks" in the genus Tringa. Its closest relative is the lesser yellowlegs, a much smaller bird with a very different appearance apart from the fine, clear, and dense pattern of the neck, which both species show in breeding plumage....

project.description:
California ornithology!  The quest for birds of all colors, shapes, and sizes!

New cover photography for 2020 by Emily (emjtca)!

https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/36999067

The photo was taken during San Francisco's Fleet Week (Oct 2019) during the Blue Angels show.


A word from Emily:  I love photography and learning new species, and then sharing what I find/capture with family and friends. iNat was a natural extension of this. I really appreciate the number of members who ID and the number of people willing to discuss an ID to further the community knowledge. I also get to see all the amazing species we share this planet with and I'm inspired to go out and spend more time outside.
